This paper deals with the analysis of external memory data structures, specifically external hash tables. The paper discusses the tradeoff between query and insertion costs in the presence of a memory buffer, which is a common topic in the field of external memory algorithms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.DB (Databases), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.AL (Computational Complexity), and cs.CC (Computational Geometry).
